					</marginalia_text>
					<person name="Stefano Guazzo"/>
					<book title="The civil conversation"/>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Guazzo's fourth book.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="EN">
				<position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						Virtu doth allwais dispose the Will, to accomplish
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						her actions reddily,
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						&amp; delectably. A nimble &amp; iollie actour.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position place="right_margin" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						A speedie, and gallant man.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						vna distinctionu[m] inter principes, et
						priuatos.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				One of the differences between princes and private citizens.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="EN">
				<position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						( A serious, &amp; cheerfull workman. )
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
		</marginalia>
		
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="left_margin" book_orientation="90">
					<marginalia_text>
						Prodest, legere sa[e]p&egrave;: repetere sa[e]pi&ugrave;s: agere sa[e]pissimi&egrave;.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				It is useful to read often, repeat more often, and to do most often.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="EN">
				<position place="right_margin" book_orientation="270">
